						<summary>

						<p>This is in modern characters and is dated in the (cyclic) year Prajōtpati. Panguni 15. It records an endowment of 200 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land by a certain Raghupati. Nāyakkar for worship of goddess Kāmākshi-Ammai. On the top of the stone is figured a lion facing the proper right.</p>						

